FT  23 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Bruntcliffe
Bruntcliffe Aggregates, the former investment holding company which came to
the market in May following its switch into reprocessed coal and aggregates,
reported profits of Pounds 132,000 pre-tax for the six months to June 30, on
sales of Pounds 305,000.
Mr David Sawyer, chairman, said the Pounds 12.5m acquisition of Northern
Scottish Quarries from Tarmac was completed in September.
Fully diluted earnings emerged at 1p. No interim is declared but, subject to
availability of reserves, a final would be recommended.
